WEBVTT

00:36.896 --> 00:38.034
[muffled] <i>Chloe!</i>

00:43.379 --> 00:44.068
<i>Chloe?</i>

00:47.896 --> 00:49.000
<i>Chloe!</i>

00:50.068 --> 00:51.344
<i>Be careful!</i>

04:11.724 --> 04:14.655
Is it okay if I speak
and we use that?

04:15.931 --> 04:17.172
- Yeah.
- Okay.

04:17.724 --> 04:21.896
My signing is adequate,
but, this will get fairly detailed.

04:24.206 --> 04:26.724
Okay, so, your address.

04:26.724 --> 04:28.586
Oh, that's Cape Cod, isn't it?

04:28.586 --> 04:29.793
Is that where you're from?

04:31.310 --> 04:32.896
No, no, I'm from Maryland.

04:32.896 --> 04:34.689
I live there with my dad.

04:34.689 --> 04:35.965
He's a doctor.

04:35.965 --> 04:38.000
That's our old, like,
summer house.

04:39.103 --> 04:41.724
I haven't been in years.
We're selling it.

04:41.724 --> 04:42.586
Oh, I see.

04:43.689 --> 04:44.862
So how did you find
out about us?

04:46.206 --> 04:49.103
Online. I've been
following your project.

04:49.103 --> 04:51.000
And no cochlear implant?

04:52.310 --> 04:54.965
No, no the timing was
never right.

04:54.965 --> 04:55.965
Oh, everyone is different.

04:57.310 --> 05:00.034
And with your hearing loss,
profile, and speech,

05:00.034 --> 05:02.724
you are an excellent candidate
for our study.

05:03.896 --> 05:05.931
I still see a speech therapist.

05:05.931 --> 05:07.206
Oh, okay.

05:08.931 --> 05:10.724
So, I have to ask.

05:12.206 --> 05:12.827
Why are you doing this?

05:13.862 --> 05:18.137
Regaining sensory ability
can be quite jarring.

05:22.413 --> 05:23.862
I remember...

05:25.068 --> 05:27.241
hearing sounds...

05:28.275 --> 05:30.000
voices and...

05:30.000 --> 05:31.655
it's still...

05:31.655 --> 05:32.620
inside me.

05:33.758 --> 05:35.793
The silence, it's just
something I've...

05:37.068 --> 05:39.034
adjusted to.

05:39.034 --> 05:40.689
But this...

05:42.103 --> 05:43.620
this is mine!

05:45.862 --> 05:46.655
Okay.

05:48.034 --> 05:50.758
Well, this is a stage one
clinical trial.

05:50.758 --> 05:53.827
Right now, once mature
auditory nerve cells are damaged,

05:53.827 --> 05:54.896
that's it.

05:54.896 --> 05:55.862
Hearing loss is irreversible.

05:57.172 --> 05:59.896
The purpose of this study
is to change that.

06:05.724 --> 06:07.896
<i>We are using
an experimental gene editing technique</i>

06:07.896 --> 06:10.379
<i>that mimics prenatal cellular growth
in the inner ear.</i>

06:16.068 --> 06:17.379
<i>The procedure itself is
relatively simple.</i>

06:18.724 --> 06:22.275
<i>A stem cell-associated
retrovirus
is injected into your inner ear.</i>

06:27.896 --> 06:31.344
<i>This retrovirus will "infect"
the surrounding tissue</i>

06:31.344 --> 06:34.206
<i>with a gene responsible
for auditory cell growth.</i>

06:43.965 --> 06:47.137
<i>The damaged nerve fibers
will grow back, restored.</i>

06:50.379 --> 06:54.344
<i>And your sense of
hearing will return.</i>

07:14.931 --> 07:15.793
<i>You can probably take
those bandages off now.</i>

07:17.413 --> 07:20.379
Just wait to put your hearing aids
back in until tomorrow.

07:22.206 --> 07:24.034
It could be weeks until
we see results.

07:25.000 --> 07:26.172
Kind of like a cold.

07:26.172 --> 07:28.310
We have to allow it to
run its course.

07:29.896 --> 07:30.931
Oh!

07:30.931 --> 07:32.034
Alright,

07:33.137 --> 07:35.379
use these drops twice a day.

07:35.379 --> 07:37.448
Once in the morning and
once at night.

07:37.448 --> 07:39.103
Okay.

07:39.103 --> 07:42.068
It's a steroidal solution
to increase cell growth

07:42.068 --> 07:43.344
and slow the immune response.

07:44.482 --> 07:47.413
You might experience
some minor side effects.

07:47.413 --> 07:52.241
Increased heart rate, light headedness,
dizziness, but nothing too serious.

07:57.275 --> 07:59.137
We're being hopeful.

08:00.448 --> 08:02.000
But, please remember that

08:03.379 --> 08:07.000
there is a strong possibility
this may not work.

08:10.862 --> 08:11.862
Okay.

08:15.275 --> 08:16.241
Oh!

08:17.482 --> 08:20.000
Here you go. This is my card.

08:20.000 --> 08:23.931
Please don't hesitate to email
or text me
if you have any questions or problems.

08:25.034 --> 08:26.034
Okay.

09:53.103 --> 09:54.206
I'm Chloe.

11:24.275 --> 11:25.413
<i>Chloe!</i>

11:53.379 --> 11:54.551
<i>Chloe!</i>

11:57.655 --> 11:59.137
Mom!

12:00.344 --> 12:01.413
<i>Be careful!</i>

15:50.206 --> 15:51.551
<i>Chloe!</i>

15:55.758 --> 15:57.379
<i>Be careful!</i>

20:57.241 --> 20:58.758
<i>Chloe!</i>

21:05.275 --> 21:06.620
Mom!

21:09.034 --> 21:09.965
<i>Chloe!</i>

22:06.172 --> 22:07.586
Hold on, hold on.

22:10.068 --> 22:12.275
Okay... okay... can you say...
can you say that again?

22:15.034 --> 22:18.758
I'm Hank Fowler,
your dad called me about the
water heater.

22:21.896 --> 22:22.862
Right.

22:24.137 --> 22:25.172
Yes, yes.

22:26.206 --> 22:26.931
Thank you.

22:27.896 --> 22:29.931
Yep. Sorry to startle you.

22:39.034 --> 22:40.137
Oh!

22:41.172 --> 22:41.896
You're little Chloe?

22:43.241 --> 22:46.172
Last time I saw you you
were yay high.

22:47.724 --> 22:49.310
Yeah, that was like
twelve years ago.

22:51.724 --> 22:54.034
How are you doing with your...

22:55.068 --> 22:56.068
I've adjusted.

22:57.896 --> 23:00.137
Your dad said you were
in town for some sort of...

23:00.931 --> 23:02.275
study.

23:02.275 --> 23:03.724
Yeah.

23:04.275 --> 23:05.724
To restore my hearing.

23:07.103 --> 23:08.275
They can do that?

23:08.275 --> 23:09.586
Not yet.

23:10.758 --> 23:13.137
It's an experiment, but
we're hopeful.

23:15.965 --> 23:17.655
Good luck with that, wow.

23:19.068 --> 23:20.344
I can get you hot water.

23:22.206 --> 23:23.827
It's in...
I know...

23:49.862 --> 23:51.000
Should be good here.

23:52.172 --> 23:53.103
Okay.

23:58.172 --> 23:59.793
Your dad said you're
looking to sell the place.

24:01.068 --> 24:03.724
I know he tried the
Airbnb thing.

24:04.965 --> 24:06.793
Y-yeah...

24:06.793 --> 24:08.655
yeah, it's just too far for us.

24:09.896 --> 24:11.103
It's time.

24:11.103 --> 24:12.000
Yeah...

24:12.482 --> 24:13.965
I'd say.

24:14.827 --> 24:15.965
All right, well,

24:15.965 --> 24:18.931
if you need anything,
just let me know.

24:21.068 --> 24:22.655
Actually there is one thing.

24:28.206 --> 24:29.965
All right, give it a try.

24:35.379 --> 24:36.206
That's the Swedes for you.

24:37.034 --> 24:38.931
This is older than you are.

24:42.758 --> 24:46.034
I wouldn't drive it back to Maryland
without having it looked at first.

24:48.310 --> 24:49.758
Should have the roads
to yourself this time of year.

24:51.068 --> 24:54.275
Though the off season could get
lonely if you're not used to it.

24:55.448 --> 24:58.241
I saw a light on across
the marsh last night.

25:02.068 --> 25:03.413
Could be late renters.

25:03.827 --> 25:06.793
Though the addicts
like to squat in empty houses.

25:08.034 --> 25:09.448
There's a problem
with that here.

25:14.103 --> 25:15.344
You'll be okay.

25:15.344 --> 25:18.793
I'm down at the harbor most days,
they made me Harbormaster.

25:20.172 --> 25:22.758
If you need anything,
I'm a call away.

25:24.137 --> 25:25.379
Or a text.

25:25.379 --> 25:26.724
I do that too.

25:28.275 --> 25:30.310
Yeah. My dad gave me
your number.

25:31.241 --> 25:32.344
Thanks.

30:49.206 --> 30:50.793
- Can I help you with something?
- Oh.

30:52.103 --> 30:52.689
Yeah.

30:53.413 --> 30:54.655
Is that your truck?

30:56.724 --> 30:57.758
It is.

30:59.620 --> 31:01.586
I'm cleaning out our
old house and...

31:02.517 --> 31:04.000
I could use a truck.

31:07.413 --> 31:08.379
I know you.

31:09.344 --> 31:10.344
Your name is Chloe, right?

31:11.586 --> 31:14.172
We used to play
together as kids.

31:14.172 --> 31:15.275
I'm Joshua.

31:18.344 --> 31:19.620
Do you remember me?

31:21.379 --> 31:22.482
Yeah.

31:24.758 --> 31:26.448
You got real sick

31:26.448 --> 31:28.103
and you lost your hearing
and you never came back.

31:30.103 --> 31:32.206
We were wondering what
was going to happen to your house.

31:33.310 --> 31:35.482
Sorry, can you hear
me right now?

31:45.793 --> 31:46.689
Hmm.

31:50.931 --> 31:51.827
Uh.

31:52.758 --> 31:53.827
Do you live here?

31:55.172 --> 31:56.103
Yeah.

31:56.724 --> 31:58.206
My mom still owns them.

32:01.172 --> 32:03.379
I told her I thought
I saw you the other day.

32:04.448 --> 32:05.172
You should come say hi.

32:06.517 --> 32:08.448
She didn't believe
that you were really back.

32:12.448 --> 32:13.724
She ain't gonna bite.

32:14.862 --> 32:15.862
Come on.

32:38.758 --> 32:40.172
Mom.

32:40.172 --> 32:41.413
Brought the Grayden girl.

32:41.931 --> 32:42.827
Chloe.

32:44.689 --> 32:45.896
Told you she was back.

32:50.965 --> 32:52.482
Isn't she deaf?

32:54.241 --> 32:56.724
She is, but she makes do.

33:02.827 --> 33:03.827
Hello.

33:04.896 --> 33:06.310
I'm Ellen.

33:07.448 --> 33:10.275
I used to watch you
when you were a toddler.

33:12.793 --> 33:14.137
I knew your mother.

33:15.724 --> 33:17.517
We went to high school together.

33:18.758 --> 33:20.310
Before she met your dad.

33:25.827 --> 33:26.517
How's he doing?

33:27.827 --> 33:29.896
He'll be out here in a
couple of weeks.

33:32.034 --> 33:33.310
We're trying to sell the house.

33:34.241 --> 33:35.344
Sounds about right.

33:38.000 --> 33:38.965
Joshua.

33:40.379 --> 33:41.827
- Joshua!
- What?

33:41.827 --> 33:44.172
There's that picture of
the two of you.

33:46.000 --> 33:47.655
Can you get it?

33:47.655 --> 33:49.344
I want Chloe to see it!

33:49.344 --> 33:50.965
Where is it?

33:50.965 --> 33:53.827
It's in the yellow album
with the stack of old photos.

34:04.896 --> 34:07.724
Your dad stopped coming
out here after your mom...

34:11.517 --> 34:12.862
Can't blame him.

34:14.448 --> 34:15.931
It's real hard to take.

34:19.034 --> 34:20.379
It's still tough on him.

34:21.965 --> 34:23.862
We thought she'd just run off.

34:25.034 --> 34:26.379
Never heard from her?

34:26.862 --> 34:27.724
No.

34:28.827 --> 34:29.827
Nothing.

34:30.896 --> 34:32.000
Nothing.

34:34.793 --> 34:36.275
You look just like her.

34:39.689 --> 34:41.620
It's like seeing a ghost.

34:41.620 --> 34:42.896
Found it.

34:46.068 --> 34:46.965
Look.

34:50.448 --> 34:51.655
I remember this.

35:49.000 --> 35:50.034
<i>Chloe.</i>

35:52.000 --> 35:53.689
<i>Say Happy Fourth of July.</i>

35:53.689 --> 35:55.413
<i>Happy
Fourth of July!</i>

36:14.827 --> 36:16.758
<i>Say Happy
Fourth of July.</i>

36:16.758 --> 36:18.000
<i>Happy
Fourth of July!</i>

36:36.724 --> 36:37.827
<i>Chloe.</i>

36:41.620 --> 36:42.586
Mom?

40:16.758 --> 40:17.896
Hey.

40:23.310 --> 40:24.620
Hey!

42:55.068 --> 42:56.000
<i>Hello?</i>

42:57.310 --> 42:58.275
<i>Chloe?</i>

42:58.275 --> 42:59.068
Dad.

43:00.172 --> 43:01.379
<i>How are you calling me?</i>

43:02.965 --> 43:03.862
<i>Wait.</i>

43:03.862 --> 43:04.965
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

43:10.206 --> 43:11.103
Yeah!

43:13.137 --> 43:14.206
I can hear you.

43:15.793 --> 43:16.896
I think it's working.

43:17.379 --> 43:18.724
<i>Oh, my god.</i>

43:19.793 --> 43:21.000
<i>This is incredible...</i>

43:25.034 --> 43:25.931
Well say something, please!

43:27.103 --> 43:29.482
<i>I'm actually at a
loss for words.</i>

43:30.965 --> 43:32.413
<i>I'm so happy for you.</i>

43:34.896 --> 43:35.862
<i>I can't believe this is real.</i>

43:37.034 --> 43:39.206
<i>After all this time, you
can hear again.</i>

44:26.344 --> 44:27.551
<i>This is better
than we could have ever expected.</i>

44:28.620 --> 44:32.448
There's activity in 80 percent
of the damaged cells

44:32.448 --> 44:34.379
along with new growth
in the surrounding tissue.

44:35.172 --> 44:37.310
This is remarkable progress

44:37.310 --> 44:39.034
and so quickly, I mean...

44:39.034 --> 44:41.172
the range, the frequencies,
it's...

44:41.172 --> 44:42.448
truly astonishing.

44:43.206 --> 44:44.827
I mean I can hear like...

44:45.413 --> 44:47.034
everything!

44:47.034 --> 44:49.551
My voice has changed
so much and your voice is

44:50.965 --> 44:53.344
different than what
I imagined it to sound like.

44:54.310 --> 44:55.482
In a good way, I hope.

44:55.482 --> 44:58.965
Yes, yes, it's fine,
it's beautiful.

45:00.379 --> 45:01.931
It's just different.

45:03.241 --> 45:05.482
Well, yes, this can be overwhelming.

45:05.482 --> 45:08.103
We have therapists
who can help with the transition.

45:10.517 --> 45:14.000
I can always hear
things in my dreams,

45:14.000 --> 45:17.137
like memories and people,
is that... weird?

45:17.620 --> 45:19.931
No.

45:19.931 --> 45:21.655
No, you were old enough to remember
sounds when you lost your hearing.

45:21.655 --> 45:22.620
Not weird at all.

45:23.482 --> 45:24.551
Okay.

45:26.344 --> 45:27.172
So what now?

45:28.482 --> 45:30.482
Just keep doing what
you're doing.

45:30.482 --> 45:33.344
Keep using the drops
and if anything changes,

45:33.344 --> 45:35.034
anything at all, just...

45:37.034 --> 45:39.206
well, I guess, just call me.

45:41.241 --> 45:42.379
Woah. Yeah.

46:03.034 --> 46:04.206
Excuse me.

47:25.206 --> 47:26.448
Been awhile.

47:28.517 --> 47:30.206
Another one's gone missing.

47:32.068 --> 47:33.034
What do you mean?

47:35.620 --> 47:37.724
Cleaning up after her shift,

47:37.724 --> 47:39.103
never came home.

47:41.379 --> 47:43.413
No car, no body...

47:45.793 --> 47:47.000
No trace.

47:51.620 --> 47:53.206
Flying south for the winter.

47:55.172 --> 47:58.551
They use the earth's magnetic fields
for their migratory patterns.

48:02.241 --> 48:03.241
This place...

48:04.344 --> 48:05.620
it does things to you.

48:09.448 --> 48:10.379
Yeah.

48:19.551 --> 48:20.448
Wait...

48:22.586 --> 48:24.068
could you hear me?

48:38.413 --> 48:39.689
<i>Hey guys!</i>

48:44.310 --> 48:46.793
<i>Hello,
how are you?</i>

48:46.793 --> 48:49.137
<i>How are you?</i>

48:50.103 --> 48:51.689
<i>It smells funny in here.</i>

49:18.344 --> 49:19.413
<i>Chloe?</i>

49:19.413 --> 49:22.413
<i>Sweetie, you got to
go back to bed.</i>

49:56.482 --> 49:57.448
Hello?

50:01.655 --> 50:03.241
Hello? Is somebody there?

50:23.724 --> 50:24.896
Who is this?

55:07.689 --> 55:10.862
[barely audible] <i>Chloe?
Say happy 4th of July.</i>

55:13.137 --> 55:14.724
<i>Say happy 4th of July.</i>

55:15.827 --> 55:17.482
<i>Say happy 4th of July.</i>

55:23.517 --> 55:24.620
<i>Chloe?</i>

55:29.103 --> 55:32.000
<i>Sweetie, you have to go back to bed.</i>

56:25.103 --> 56:26.965
That's our wall
of shame there.

56:31.068 --> 56:33.896
Am I crazy or is that treatment
you're doing working?

56:38.310 --> 56:39.793
Yeah, it is.

56:42.655 --> 56:43.724
Ain't that something!

56:45.000 --> 56:46.551
It's freezing out here!

56:46.551 --> 56:48.034
You want a fisherman's warm up?

56:50.206 --> 56:51.103
Come on.

56:58.344 --> 56:59.241
Here you go.

57:12.000 --> 57:13.827
It's good for what ails you.

57:20.896 --> 57:22.000
So how does it feel?

57:23.172 --> 57:24.862
Hearing after all this time.

57:26.103 --> 57:27.586
Still getting used to it.

57:29.241 --> 57:30.758
I forgot how noisy the world is.

57:32.862 --> 57:34.000
Ain't that the truth.

57:37.689 --> 57:39.103
I saw you in a uniform.

57:39.103 --> 57:40.655
In my dad's old pictures.

57:42.206 --> 57:44.172
I... I didn't know
you were police.

57:44.172 --> 57:44.862
Huh.

57:45.655 --> 57:47.000
Was police.

57:47.275 --> 57:51.655
Some junkie decided
to give me an early retirement.

57:52.724 --> 57:53.862
Medals and all.

57:54.827 --> 57:55.965
Probably for the best.

57:57.793 --> 57:58.689
As a cop you...

57:59.862 --> 58:02.172
see things most people
don't get to see.

58:03.758 --> 58:05.000
I don't miss it really.

58:12.000 --> 58:13.068
We looked for your mom.

58:14.068 --> 58:15.310
It was really hard to do.

58:18.379 --> 58:19.586
Yeah...

58:22.344 --> 58:24.793
That's the last time I remember
really hearing anything.

58:28.862 --> 58:30.241
I still hear her voice.

58:38.793 --> 58:39.827
I...

58:40.965 --> 58:42.310
I wanted to tell you something.

58:44.103 --> 58:45.724
I saw you the other day

58:47.068 --> 58:48.655
with Joshua. -Ellen's

58:48.655 --> 58:50.034
boy.
- Oh.

58:50.034 --> 58:51.724
You might want to be
careful around them.

58:52.689 --> 58:54.000
He's been in some trouble.

58:55.206 --> 58:56.793
What kind of trouble?

58:56.793 --> 58:57.724
Uh...

59:04.000 --> 59:06.379
A few years back, uh...

59:07.448 --> 59:09.000
some pets were going missing.

59:09.000 --> 59:11.103
Dogs, primarily.

59:11.103 --> 59:12.758
All over the outer Cape.

59:14.034 --> 59:14.931
They couldn't prove it, but...

59:16.206 --> 59:18.137
I felt like he had
something to do with it.

59:19.896 --> 59:22.172
Him and his ma,
they're wired funny.

59:24.896 --> 59:26.241
She's had a rough go of it.

59:29.206 --> 59:30.137
Yeah.

59:31.172 --> 59:32.206
Thanks for the heads up.

59:33.172 --> 59:34.758
Hey, don't mention it.

59:42.206 --> 59:43.344
Hank...

59:49.310 --> 59:50.965
Do you have a drill
I can borrow?

